<subSubSection pageNumber="354" type="discussion">
<paragraph pageNumber="354">
<emphasis italics="true" pageNumber="354">Note:</emphasis>
This was treated as the 
<typeStatus>generitype</typeStatus>
of 
<taxonomicName class="Magnoliopsida" family="Nyctaginaceae" genus="Boerhavia" kingdom="Plantae" order="Caryophyllales" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageNumber="354">Boerhavia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
by Standley (in 
<emphasis italics="true" pageNumber="354">Contr. U. S. Natl. Herb.</emphasis>
12: 375. 1909). However, under Art. 10.5, Ex. 7 (a voted example) of the Vienna Code, this is a type choice made under the American Code and is to be replaced under Art. 10.5b by 
<normalizedToken originalValue="Hitchcockâ€™s">Hitchcock's</normalizedToken>
choice 
<emphasis italics="true" pageNumber="354">(Prop. Brit. Bot.</emphasis>
: 115. 1929) of 
<taxonomicName authority="L." authorityName="Linnaeus" authorityYear="1753" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Nyctaginaceae" genus="Boerhavia" kingdom="Plantae" order="Caryophyllales" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="diffusa">
<emphasis italics="true" pageNumber="354">B. diffusa</emphasis>
L.
</taxonomicName>
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageNumber="354" type="multiple">
<paragraph pageNumber="354">
Gilbert (in Jarvis &amp; al, 
<emphasis italics="true" pageNumber="354">Regnum Veg.</emphasis>
127: 25. 1993) formally designated 9.1 (LINN) as a 
<typeStatus>neotype</typeStatus>
. However, under Art. 9.8, earlier choices of this post-1753 sheet as 
<typeStatus>lectotype</typeStatus>
are to be corrected, and that of Fawcett &amp; Rendle appears to be the earliest.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
